
Software Services Agreement
Core name: Bioinformatics Core
	
THIS SOFTWARE  SERVICES AGREEMENT and the included SCHEDULE (“Agreement”) is entered into this XXth day of YYY, 2019 (“Effective Date”) by and between University of Massachusetts, a public institution of higher education of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, as represented by and solely on behalf of its Medical School and Bioinformatics Core Facility, having it offices at 55 Lake Avenue North, Worcester, MA 01655. (“UMass” and interchangeably as “Institution”) and, Skyhawk Therapeutics, Inc., with a place of business at 35 Gatehouse Drive, Waltham MA (“Company”); (hereinafter UMass and Company may be individually referred to as a “Party” and collectively as the “Parties”).

WHEREAS;
University of Massachusetts Medical School, as a not-for-profit, public entity of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, is able to provide the services desired by Company only as provided by and contracted through its identified “Core” Laboratory Facilities.

Company wishes to obtain a license to use the Software developed and owned by UMass, as well as to procure services in relation to the maintenance of said Software, as further defined below; and

UMass is willing to grant to the Company a non-exclusive, non-transferable License to use the Software for the term and specific purpose set forth in this Agreement; and

The Software content in relation to this Agreement is known as: DolphinNext Interface Software (hereinafter, the “Software”)

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing, and of the mutual promises and undertakings contained herein, and other good and valuable consideration, the parties agree as follows:

	In consideration of the mutual covenants and promises set forth below, the parties agree as follows:
1.	Software-associated Services
1.1.	Statement of Work. All services to be provided by Institution, other than those contained within this Agreement (“Services”) will be set forth in a written statement of work (“Statement of Work”) signed by authorized representatives of both parties.  Each Statement of Work will set forth the description of the Services to be done and the hourly, daily or other fees for the Services to be performed, and other matters as the parties may agree upon.  A template Statement of Work is attached to this Agreement as “Schedule 1”.  
1.2.	Provisions of Services. Institution agrees to use reasonable efforts to provide the Services to Company in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement and the applicable Statements of Work.  Services to be provided pursuant to this Agreement (not including the addition of any Statement(s) of Work) are as follows:
A maximum of 4 (four) hours per month, of software maintenance and support (“Support”).  Support may include provision of technical advice and/or any questions answered by Institution as presented by Company.  
Any further and/or subsequent Support (“Additional Support”), as desired by Company, shall require a Statement of Work to be agreed upon between the Parties, in addition to this Agreement, as provided for in Schedule 1.
1.3.	Description of Software. Services to be provided will be in relation to the Software referred to as “Dolphin Next” and further described below:
“DolphinNext is a data processing platform that processes the samples in sequencing experiments which require automated data processing pipeline. DolphinNext allows users with little bioinformatics knowledge to process their own data on their preferred computational environment with a user-friendly web interface.”  

1.4.	Format of Installation. DolphinNext Software will be installed and maintained by UMass Biocore team into a preferred server in Company. (No delivery by electronic transfer, U.S. postal mailing, or otherwise, shall occur).  Unless expressly included in a particular Statement of Work or otherwise agreed in writing, Institution is not obligated to provide any Additional Support or maintenance services for any deliverables other than those provided pursuant to this Agreement.
1.5.	Estimated Times. The parties agree that, unless otherwise expressly stated in a particular Statement of Work or otherwise agreed in writing, where a time or amount of Services required for a particular task or deliverable is described in a Statement of Work, it is an estimate only.  Institution will use reasonable efforts to advise Company as soon as is practicable if the time or amount of Services required is likely to exceed the estimate.
1.6.	Approved Purpose. Company will use DolphinNext in relation to existing process and pipelines as well as to create new ones. Company may also use DolphinNext to run these pipelines to process their data in their preferred servers and track the run results using this interface.  Company shall be permitted to use the Software for the aforementioned Approved Purpose in relation to the Description of the Software as they so choose so long as Company’s use of the Software remains internal to Company.
The Approved Purpose shall be solely for use by the Company and shall not be resold, assigned, modified, duplicated, or sublicensed to any party for any reason.  Use by Company shall be limited to internal business use and no external use shall be provided for as an Approved Purposes.
Notwithstanding the foregoing, Institution agrees that (a) Company shall be permitted to demonstrate its use of the Software at meetings with third parties, and (b) third party contractors or consultants shall have the right to use the Software for or on behalf of Company.
