3.2.	If applicable, Company will reimburse Institution for reasonable out-of-pocket expenses incurred in the provision of Services, including, without limitation, all travel, accommodation, and meal expenses for Services performed at Company site or Company’s client’s site, to the extent approved by Company in advance or set forth in the applicable Statement of Work.
3.3.	Institution will render invoices to Company, indicating the Services for which the invoice is rendered, the period of time it covers, the fees due, and any other additions, expenses or taxes (evidenced by receipts), and any other detail reasonably required for Company to verify the amount invoiced.  All invoices submitted under this Agreement and the Statements of Work will refer to this Agreement and the applicable Statement of Work.
3.4.	Company will pay all invoices within thirty (30) days of receipt, except for such invoices that Company disputes, with respect to which the following procedures shall apply. In the event that Company wishes to dispute an item or items on an invoice, Company will notify Institution in writing within fourteen days of receipt of that invoice, setting out its reasons in reasonable detail.  If no notice of dispute is received by Institution fourteen days after receipt of an invoice by Company, the invoice will be deemed accepted, and Company will be obliged to pay the invoice in accordance with its terms.  In case of a dispute regarding billing, Company must pay all undisputed charges and items.
3.5.	Company is responsible for all taxes due of Company resulting from the Services.
3.6.	If Company fails to pay any amount payable by it under this Agreement and not the subject of a dispute as set forth above within 30 days of receipt of an invoice, Institution will be entitled to charge and Company will pay 1.50% interest per month (or if less the highest legal rate), compounded daily, on the overdue amount.
